    <statement><div><p>Simplify the expression below using the law of negative indices:</p>

<p><me>
{6}{b}^{-{1}}
</me></p>

<p>Give your answer without negative indices.</p>

<p><fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  </p></div></statement>
    <solution><div><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>The negative index law states:</p>

<p><me>
a^{-n} = \frac{1}{a^n}.
</me></p>

<p>Applying this to the expression:</p>

<p><me>
{6}{b}^{-{1}} 
= {6} \times \frac{1}{ {b}^{1} }.
</me></p>

<p>So the simplified form is:</p>

<p><me>
\frac{ {6} }{ {b}^{1} }.
</me></p></div></solution>
    <answer><p><m>\frac{6}{b}</m></p></answer>
